        <name>mute</name>
        <qualifiedname>bt_micp_mic_ctlr_cb::mute</qualifiedname>
        <briefdescription>
<para>Callback function for Microphone Control Profile mute. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Called when the value is read, or if the value is changed by either the Microphone Device or a Microphone Controller.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>mic_ctlr</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Microphone Controller instance pointer. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>err</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Error value. 0 on success, GATT error or errno on fail. For notifications, this will always be 0. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>mute</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>The mute setting of the Microphone Control Service. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
